act.article:
2 Definitions.—In these rules, unless the context 
otherwise requires,—



a
“Act” means the Wild Life (Protection) Act, 1972 (53 of 1972);   


b “Chairperson” means the Chairperson 
of the Tiger Conservation Authority;   


c
“Fund” means the Tiger Conservation Authority Fund constituted under 
sub-section (2) of section 38Q;  



d
“member” means a member of the Tiger Conservation Authority;   


e
“Member-Secretary” means the Member-Secretary of the Tiger Conservation 
Authority;   


f
“section” means section of the Act;  



g
“Tiger Conservation Authority” means the National Tiger Conservation 
Authority constituted under section 38L;  


       h
“Vice-Chairperson” means the Vice-Chairperson of the Tiger Conservation 
Authority.
